e":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/#/schema/person/image/","url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/garlic-zest-logo.webp","contentUrl":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/garlic-zest-logo.webp","width":440,"height":182,"caption":"Lisa Lotts"},"logo":{"@id":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/#/schema/person/image/"},"description":"Lisa founded Garlic &amp; Zest in 2013, a Food and Cooking website featuring over 1000 tested recipes. Her modern family fare has been featured in HuffPost, Parade, Today.com, Oprah Daily, Better Homes and Gardens, Men's Journal, BuzzFeed and Shape, to name a few.","sameAs":["https://www.garlicandzest.com/about/","https://www.facebook.com/garlicandzest","https://www.instagram.com/garlicandzest/","https://www.linkedin.com/company/garlic-zest/","https://www.pinterest.com/GarlicandZest/","https://www.youtube.com/@GarlicandZest"],"award":["Winner","Best Recipe Blogger","South Florida Blogger Awards","2016. Semi-finaliist 2017","2018","2019"]},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#faq-question-1733160725505","position":1,"url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#faq-question-1733160725505","name":"What is cinnamon streusel made of?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"In this case, sugar, flour, spices, and butter. A lot of butter. Many streusel recipes use cold butter and cut it into a flour and sugar mixture, giving it a crumbly vibe. This recipe uses melted butter to coat the flour, which gives the topping a <a href=\"https://justcrumbcake.com/new-york-style-crumb-cake/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">New York crumb cake</a> quality.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#faq-question-1733166837157","position":2,"url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#faq-question-1733166837157","name":"Is cinnamon crumb cake the same as coffee cake?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"They are the same in that these sweets are suitable for breakfast or brunch because they usually have a streusel topping or glaze instead of thick buttercream frosting. I consider them a more laid-back version of dessert -- for breakfast or snacking.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Cinnamon Streusel Coffee Cake","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lisa Lotts"},"description":"This recipe is adapted from Sara Foster&#039;s New York Style Crumb Cake.  I&#039;ve added toasted pecans and extra salt (in both the cake batter and cinnamon streusel). The salt mediates the sweet flavor and adds depth to this cinnamon streusel coffee cake.","datePublished":"2024-12-03T14:26:00+00:00","image":["https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-23.jpg","https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-23-500x500.jpg","https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-23-500x375.jpg","https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-23-480x270.jpg"],"video":{"name":"Cinnamon Streusel Coffee Cake","description":"If you like streusel coffee cake that's piled high with cinnamon streusel topping, this New York Crumb Cake is outstanding!\nIt has a thin layer of plush vanilla-scented cake and an unholy amount of cinnamon pecan streusel.\n\nWe add sea salt to balance the sweetness and toasted pecans for extra texture and satisfying crunch.\n\nGet the full printable recipe as well as tips and substitutions here: https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/\n\nCinnamon Streusel Coffee Cake (a.k.a. New York Crumb Cake)\n\nINGREDIENTS: \n\nFor Topping\n2½ cups all purpose flour\n1 cup light brown sugar firmly packed\n2¼ teaspoons cinnamon ground\n2 sticks unsalted melted butter\n1 cup pecans chopped\n½ teaspoon iodized salt\n¼ teaspoon sea salt for finishing the crumb topping.\n\nFor Cake\n1½ cups all purpose flour\n½ cup sugar\n2¼ teaspoons baking powder\n½ teaspoon salt\n½ + 2 tablespoons cup plus 2 tablespoons milk\n1 large egg\n2 tablespoons canola oil\n2½ teaspoons vanilla extract\n2-3 tablespoons confectioner’s sugar for garnish\n\nDIRECTIONS:\n\nTOAST THE PECANS:\nPreheat the oven to 350° F and spread 1 cup pecans into a single layer on a baking sheet. Bake for 8-10 minutes until the pecans are toasted and fragrant. Remove from the oven and roughly chop.\n\nPREPARE THE BAKING PAN:\nReduce the oven temperature to 325° F.\nSpray an 11×7″ baking pan with vegetable spray and line the bottom and sides with parchment paper. (Cut the paper 7″ wide and about 16″ long so that the bottom is covered and there is an overhang on either side of the pan.)\n\nFOR THE CINNAMON STREUSEL TOPPING:\nIn a large bowl, combine 2½ cups all purpose flour, 1 cup light brown sugar, 2¼ teaspoons cinnamon, ½ teaspoon iodized salt and whisk to blend. Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and add 2 sticks unsalted melted butter to it. Mix to combine.\nAdd the chopped toasted pecans to the crumble mixture and toss with your clean hands until well combined. The topping should have a loose, crumbly consistency. Set aside.\n\nFOR THE CAKE LAYER:\nAdd1½ cups all purpose flour, ½ cup sugar, 2¼ teaspoons baking powder and ½ teaspoon salt to a small bowl – and whisk to combine.\n\nIn a medium bowl, whisk together ½ + 2 tablespoons cup plus 2 tablespoons milk, 2 tablespoons canola oil, 1 large egg and 2½ teaspoons vanilla extract. \n\nAdd the flour mixture to the wet ingredients and stir just until combined.\nPour the cake batter into the prepared pan and spread into an even layer with a rubber spatula.\n\nAdd the crumble topping evenly across the batter. (It will look like you’ve got WAY TOO MUCH topping — but use it all.) Sprinkle the crumble with ¼ teaspoon sea salt.\n\nBake for 35-40 minutes until the cake rises and the topping bakes into the dough.\n\nRemove from the oven and cool slightly in the pan. Run a knife along the edge to loosen the cake and lift it from the pan to a cutting board. Cut into squares. Sprinkle with 2-3 tablespoons confectioner’s sugar if desired and serve.","uploadDate":"2024-12-03T19:35:08+00:00","duration":"PT1M16S","thumbnailUrl":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7ua1vx58Qdw/hqdefault.jpg","embedUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/embed/7ua1vx58Qdw?feature=oembed","contentUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7ua1vx58Qdw","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["15"],"prepTime":"PT20M","cookTime":"PT35M","totalTime":"PT60M","recipeIngredient":["2½ cups all purpose flour","1 cup light brown sugar (firmly packed)","2¼ teaspoons cinnamon (ground)","2 sticks unsalted melted butter","1 cup pecans (chopped)","½ teaspoon iodized salt","¼ teaspoon  sea salt (for finishing the crumb topping.)","1½ cups all purpose flour","½ cup sugar","2¼ teaspoons baking powder","½ teaspoon salt","½ cup plus 2 tablespoons milk","1 large egg","2 tablespoons canola oil","2½ teaspoons vanilla extract","2-3 tablespoons confectioner's sugar (for garnish)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"TOAST THE PECANS:","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Preheat the oven to 350° F and spread 1 cup pecans into a single layer on a baking sheet. Bake for 8-10 minutes until the pecans are toasted and fragrant. Remove from the oven and roughly chop.","name":"Preheat the oven to 350° F and spread 1 cup pecans into a single layer on a baking sheet. Bake for 8-10 minutes until the pecans are toasted and fragrant. Remove from the oven and roughly chop.","url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#wprm-recipe-26262-step-0-0"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"PREPARE THE BAKING PAN:","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Reduce the oven temperature to 325° F.","name":"Reduce the oven temperature to 325° F.","url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#wprm-recipe-26262-step-1-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Spray an 11x7&quot; baking pan with vegetable spray and line the bottom and sides with parchment paper. (Cut the paper 7&quot; wide and about 16&quot; long so that the bottom is covered and there is an overhang on either side of the pan.)","name":"Spray an 11x7&quot; baking pan with vegetable spray and line the bottom and sides with parchment paper. (Cut the paper 7&quot; wide and about 16&quot; long so that the bottom is covered and there is an overhang on either side of the pan.)","url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#wprm-recipe-26262-step-1-1"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"FOR THE CINNAMON STREUSEL TOPPING:","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a large bowl, combine 2½ cups all purpose flour, 1 cup light brown sugar, 2¼ teaspoons cinnamon, ½ teaspoon iodized salt and whisk to blend.  Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and add 2 sticks unsalted melted butter to it.  Mix to combine.","name":"In a large bowl, combine 2½ cups all purpose flour, 1 cup light brown sugar, 2¼ teaspoons cinnamon, ½ teaspoon iodized salt and whisk to blend.  Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and add 2 sticks unsalted melted butter to it.  Mix to combine.","url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#wprm-recipe-26262-step-2-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the chopped toasted pecans to the crumble mixture and toss with your clean hands until well combined.  The topping should have a loose, crumbly consistency.  Set aside.","name":"Add the chopped toasted pecans to the crumble mixture and toss with your clean hands until well combined.  The topping should have a loose, crumbly consistency.  Set aside.","url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#wprm-recipe-26262-step-2-1"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"FOR THE CAKE LAYER:","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add1½ cups all purpose flour,  ½ cup sugar, 2¼ teaspoons baking powder and ½ teaspoon salt to a small bowl - and whisk to combine.","name":"Add1½ cups all purpose flour,  ½ cup sugar, 2¼ teaspoons baking powder and ½ teaspoon salt to a small bowl - and whisk to combine.","url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#wprm-recipe-26262-step-3-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a medium bowl, whisk together ½ cup plus 2 tablespoons milk, 2 tablespoons canola oil, 1 large egg and 2½ teaspoons vanilla extract.  Add the flour mixture to the wet ingredients and stir just until combined.","name":"In a medium bowl, whisk together ½ cup plus 2 tablespoons milk, 2 tablespoons canola oil, 1 large egg and 2½ teaspoons vanilla extract.  Add the flour mixture to the wet ingredients and stir just until combined.","url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#wprm-recipe-26262-step-3-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Pour the cake batter into the prepared pan and spread into an even layer with a rubber spatula.","name":"Pour the cake batter into the prepared pan and spread into an even layer with a rubber spatula.","url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#wprm-recipe-26262-step-3-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the crumble topping evenly across the batter.  (It will look like you&#39;ve got WAY TOO MUCH topping -- but use it all.) Sprinkle the crumble with ¼ teaspoon  sea salt.","name":"Add the crumble topping evenly across the batter.  (It will look like you&#39;ve got WAY TOO MUCH topping -- but use it all.) Sprinkle the crumble with ¼ teaspoon  sea salt.","url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#wprm-recipe-26262-step-3-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Bake for 35-40 minutes  until the cake rises and the topping bakes into the dough.","name":"Bake for 35-40 minutes  until the cake rises and the topping bakes into the dough.","url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#wprm-recipe-26262-step-3-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Remove from the oven and cool slightly in the pan.  Run a knife along the edge to loosen the cake and lift it from the pan to a cutting board.  Cut into squares.  Sprinkle with 2-3 tablespoons confectioner's sugarf desired and serve.","name":"Remove from the oven and cool slightly in the pan.  Run a knife along the edge to loosen the cake and lift it from the pan to a cutting board.  Cut into squares.  Sprinkle with 2-3 tablespoons confectioner's sugarf desired and serve.","url":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#wprm-recipe-26262-step-3-5"}]}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.22","ratingCount":"14","reviewCount":"4"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Can you use pecans instead of walnuts","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Carter"},"datePublished":"2018-01-28"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Mmm I love cakes with a crumble topping like this, this one looks life a perfect mid morning snack","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Amy | The Cook Report"},"datePublished":"2017-08-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Oh my, I need to make this and pray very hard that I will not eat it all on the same day! :-D","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Christine"},"datePublished":"2017-08-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"That coffee cake is speaking my name! I feel more virtuous when I only use a little crumb topping, but this is the cake I really want. :) I need to put this on my holiday baking list.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Annemarie @ justalittlebitofbacon"},"datePublished":"2017-08-20"}],"recipeCategory":["Breakfast","Dessert"],"recipeCuisine":["American"],"keywords":"brunch dessert, cinnamon, coffee cake","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"409.16 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"50.87 g","proteinContent":"5.96 g","fatContent":"20.81 g","saturatedFatContent":"9.2 g","cholesterolContent":"49.67 mg","sodiumContent":"284.19 mg","fiberContent":"1.69 g","sugarContent":"24.34 g","transFatContent":"0.5 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"10.12 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https://www.garlicandzest.com/cinnamon-pecan-crumble-coffeecake/"}]}</script>
