<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column23228_0f0229-03"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<p class="kt-adv-heading23228_f560ca-2f wp-block-kadence-advancedheading" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading23228_f560ca-2f"><strong>Inside:</strong> The buttery secret to making cinnamon streusel for an authentic New York crumb cake perfect for breakfast, brunch and snacking.</p>
</div></div>

</div></div>


<p>This is the ultimate cinnamon streusel coffee cake. Its soft, sweet cake layer is topped with an unholy amount of cinnamon streusel. I add toasted pecans for a little crunch and extra salt, which enhances the sweetness and brings a heightened dimension to the flavors. Look no further than this recipe when you crave a mile-high New York crumb cake.</p>



<span id="more-23228"></span>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large aligncenter"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="819" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201024%20819'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Sliced New York crumb cake." class="wp-image-140965" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16-1024x819.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16-600x480.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16-768x614.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16-150x120.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16-1024x819.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="819" src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16-1024x819.jpg" alt="Sliced New York crumb cake." class="wp-image-140965" srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16-1024x819.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16-600x480.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16-768x614.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16-150x120.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-16.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<p>This recipe,&nbsp;adapted from&nbsp;<strong>The Foster&rsquo;s Market Cookbook</strong>, is everything a coffee cake should be: copious<em> </em>amounts of crumb topping nestled into soft sponge. You can add powdered sugar just before serving to enhance the Wow factor.</p>



<p>This isn&rsquo;t your average, so-so-crumb cake here. This is a cinnamon streusel coffee cake with a 2:1 ratio of cinnamon streusel crumb to one part cake! Like my grandmother&rsquo;s <a href="https://www.garlicandzest.com/grandmothers-puffs-southern-fry-bread-yeast/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">fried dough</a>, it&rsquo;s not an everyday treat, but well worth the calories.</p>



<p>Think of the plush base layer as a delivery method&nbsp;for getting the crumb portion to your mouth. &nbsp;</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-why-you-ll-love-this-cinnamon-streusel-coffee-cake-recipe">Why you&rsquo;ll love this cinnamon streusel coffee cake recipe</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>The texture is soft and spongy, with just enough sturdiness to support the crumb topping.</li>



<li>You don&rsquo;t need any special equipment, not even a hand mixer.</li>



<li>It delivers big on the cinnamon streusel topping and crunchy toasted pecans add another layer of flavor and texture.</li>



<li>It can be made ahead of time, freezes well, and the recipe can be doubled for bigger groups.</li>
</ul>



<div class="wp-block-group ingredients is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-ingredients-you-ll-need">Ingredients you&rsquo;ll need:</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="960" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20960'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Ingredients for new york crumb cake." class="wp-image-140961" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake.jpg 1200w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-600x480.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-1024x819.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-768x614.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-150x120.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="960" src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake.jpg" alt="Ingredients for new york crumb cake." class="wp-image-140961" srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake.jpg 1200w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-600x480.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-1024x819.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-768x614.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-150x120.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>All-Purpose Flour</strong>&ndash;I use King Arthur&rsquo;s Unbleached all-purpose flour.</li>



<li><strong>Light Brown Sugar</strong>&ndash;this is for the cinnamon streusel topping.</li>



<li><strong>Cinnamon</strong>&ndash;you can&rsquo;t make a New York crumb cake without it.</li>



<li><strong>Butter</strong>&ndash;I recommend unsalted butter for baking unless otherwise noted.</li>



<li><strong>Pecans</strong>&ndash;for a traditional New York style crumb cake, you can skip the pecans, but I like the toasted crunch it adds to the cinnamon streusel. It&rsquo;s your choice.</li>



<li><strong>Granulated Sugar</strong>&ndash;use your favorite brand.</li>



<li><strong>Baking Powder</strong>&ndash;to give rise to the cake. Be sure to check your baking powder&rsquo;s expiration date. They have a shelf life, and if yours is too old, you won&rsquo;t get the same reaction and lift. Don&rsquo;t substitute baking soda, as this recipe doesn&rsquo;t have an acid for it to react with, and it won&rsquo;t help the cake rise.</li>



<li><strong>Iodized Salt&ndash;</strong>dissolves and distributes evenly in the batter. Iodized salt is best for baking.</li>



<li><strong>Milk</strong>&ndash;I used whole milk, but a low-fat milk or dairy free milk should work fine.</li>



<li><strong>Large Eggs</strong>&ndash;for a soft, tender crumb.</li>



<li><strong>Vegetable Oil</strong>&ndash;you can also substitute canola oil. Do not use olive oil.</li>



<li><strong>Vanilla Extract</strong>&ndash;I recommend Penzey&rsquo;s Double Strength vanilla for the best vanilla flavor.</li>



<li><strong>Fine Sea Salt</strong>&ndash;for finishing the cinnamon streusel coffee cake. A dusting of sea salt over the crumb layer enhances the sweetness and balances the flavors.</li>



<li><strong>Confectioners Sugar</strong>&ndash;optional, but it adds another eye-popping sweet element.</li>
</ul>



<p><strong>Note:</strong> Allspice and nutmeg are shown in the photo above but not in the recipe. I sometimes add them to the cinnamon streusel topping for a change of pace. If you want to use them, here are the proper amounts:  4&frac14; teaspoons of cinnamon, one teaspoon of allspice and one teaspoon of nutmeg in the crumble portion of the recipe.</p>
</div>



