<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-step-by-step-instructions">Step-by-step instructions:</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large aligncenter"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="666" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201024%20666'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Assembling the cinnamon streusel." class="wp-image-140959" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-600x390.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-768x499.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-150x98.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-1024x666.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="666" src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-1024x666.jpg" alt="Assembling the cinnamon streusel." class="wp-image-140959" srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-600x390.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-768x499.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-150x98.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>In a large bowl, combine the flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and iodized salt. Whisk to combine.</li>



<li>Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and add the melted butter. Mix well until there are no dry parts and the cinnamon streusel is crumbly.</li>
</ol>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large aligncenter"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="666" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201024%20666'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Chop the toasted pecans and add them to the crumble topping." class="wp-image-140958" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-600x390.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-768x499.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-150x98.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-1024x666.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="666" src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-1024x666.jpg" alt="Chop the toasted pecans and add them to the crumble topping." class="wp-image-140958" srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-600x390.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-768x499.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-150x98.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<p>3. Toast the pecans in a 350&deg; oven for 8-10 minutes or until crunchy and fragrant.</p>



<p>4. Chop the nuts and add them to the cinnamon streusel mixture to combine.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large aligncenter"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="666" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201024%20666'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Mix the dry and swet ingredients for the cake batter." class="wp-image-140956" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2-600x390.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2-768x499.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2-150x98.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2-1024x666.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="666" src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2-1024x666.jpg" alt="Mix the dry and swet ingredients for the cake batter." class="wp-image-140956" srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2-600x390.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2-768x499.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2-150x98.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-2.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<p>5. Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl and whisk to combine.</p>



<p>6. Whisk together the milk, oil, egg and vanilla extract in a separate bowl.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="780" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20780'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Mix the batter until just moistened and spread into a pan." class="wp-image-140957" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3.jpg 1200w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3-600x390.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3-768x499.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3-150x98.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="780" src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3.jpg" alt="Mix the batter until just moistened and spread into a pan." class="wp-image-140957" srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3.jpg 1200w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3-600x390.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3-768x499.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3-150x98.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-2-copy-3.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<p>7. Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and stir until the batter is combined with no dry bits remaining.</p>



<p>8. Spread the batter into the prepared baking pan (7&times;11&Prime;).</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="780" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20780'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Spread the cake with crumble topping and sprinkle with sea salt." class="wp-image-140970" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9.jpg 1200w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-600x390.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-768x499.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-150x98.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="780" src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9.jpg" alt="Spread the cake with crumble topping and sprinkle with sea salt." class="wp-image-140970" srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9.jpg 1200w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-600x390.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-768x499.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9-150x98.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/9.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<p>9. Spread the crumble over the cake batter and sprinkle with sea salt. Bake for 35-40 minutes in a 350&deg; preheated oven or until a cake tester or toothpick poked into the center comes out clean.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="780" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20780'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Let the cake cool in the pan for 10-15 minutes." class="wp-image-140962" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2.jpg 1200w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2-600x390.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2-768x499.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2-150x98.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="780" src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2.jpg" alt="Let the cake cool in the pan for 10-15 minutes." class="wp-image-140962" srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2.jpg 1200w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2-600x390.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2-768x499.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2-150x98.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9-2.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<p>10. After baking, cool the New York crumb cake in the pan for 10-15 minutes before transferring it to a serving platter. Once the cake has cooled, sprinkle it with powdered sugar for a final embellishment before cutting it into slices.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group ingredients summary1 is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-pro-tips">Pro-Tips:</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>To make it easier to get the cinnamon streusel coffee cake out of the pan for serving, line it with parchment paper&nbsp;that overhangs the sides of the pan. &nbsp;Just lift the ends and transfer the cake to a cutting board or dish when it&rsquo;s cooled.</li>



<li>To make a double-batch, double the recipe and use a 12x17x1&Prime; jellyroll pan to bake it.</li>
</ul>
</div>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large aligncenter"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="681" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201024%20681'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Cinnamon streusel coffee cake on a cutting board." class="wp-image-140971" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13-600x399.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13-768x511.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13-1024x681.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="681" src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13-1024x681.jpg" alt="Cinnamon streusel coffee cake on a cutting board." class="wp-image-140971" srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13-600x399.jpg 600w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13-768x511.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-13.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<div class="wp-block-group ingredients summary1 brand-green is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-swaps-and-variations">Swaps and Variations:</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Use walnuts instead of pecans in the topping, or skip the nuts for a classic New York crumb cake.</li>



<li>Substitute one tablespoon of apple or pumpkin pie spice instead of cinnamon in the streusel topping.</li>



<li>Instead of dusting with powdered sugar, drizzle it with a glaze made with &frac12; cup of powdered sugar and two tablespoons of cream.</li>
</ul>
</div>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large aligncenter"><img decoding="async" width="819" height="1024" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20819%201024'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A slice of cinnamon streusel coffee cake." class="wp-image-140972" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17-819x1024.jpg 819w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17-480x600.jpg 480w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17-768x960.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17-150x188.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 819px) 100vw, 819px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17-819x1024.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="819" height="1024" src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17-819x1024.jpg" alt="A slice of cinnamon streusel coffee cake." class="wp-image-140972" srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17-819x1024.jpg 819w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17-480x600.jpg 480w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17-768x960.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17-150x188.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 819px) 100vw, 819px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-17.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">FAQ&rsquo;s</h2>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1733160725505"><strong class="schema-faq-question">What is cinnamon streusel made of?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">In this case, sugar, flour, spices, and butter. A lot of butter. Many streusel recipes use cold butter and cut it into a flour and sugar mixture, giving it a crumbly vibe. This recipe uses melted butter to coat the flour, which gives the topping a <a href="https://justcrumbcake.com/new-york-style-crumb-cake/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">New York crumb cake</a> quality.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1733166837157"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Is cinnamon crumb cake the same as coffee cake?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">They are the same in that these sweets are suitable for breakfast or brunch because they usually have a streusel topping or glaze instead of thick buttercream frosting. I consider them a more laid-back version of dessert &mdash; for breakfast or snacking.</p> </div> </div>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large aligncenter"><img decoding="async" width="681" height="1024" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20681%201024'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Sprinkled with powdered sugar." class="wp-image-140973" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19-681x1024.jpg 681w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19-399x600.jpg 399w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19-768x1155.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19-1022x1536.jpg 1022w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19-150x226.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 681px) 100vw, 681px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19-681x1024.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="681" height="1024" src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19-681x1024.jpg" alt="Sprinkled with powdered sugar." class="wp-image-140973" srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19-681x1024.jpg 681w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19-399x600.jpg 399w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19-768x1155.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19-1022x1536.jpg 1022w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19-150x226.jpg 150w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 681px) 100vw, 681px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-19.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<div class="wp-block-group ingredients summary2 is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-make-ahead">Make Ahead:</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>You can bake it a day ahead of time. Keep it well-wrapped on a counter at room temperature.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-storage">Storage:</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Cover the cinnamon crumb cake with foil or plastic wrap or in an airtight container and store at room temperature for 3-4 days.</li>



<li>If you store it in the fridge, I recommend taking it out to rest for 20 minutes at room temperature before enjoying it. Because the topping has so much butter, it will have more of a melt-in-your-mouth quality at room temperature.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-freezing">Freezing:</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li> Double-wrap cinnamon crumb cake well in plastic wrap and freezer paper to freeze for up to 2 months. </li>



<li>Thaw before enjoying.</li>



<li>If you plan on freezing this dessert, I recommend waiting to add powdered sugar until just before serving.</li>
</ul>
</div>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1500" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201500'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A thick slice of new york style crumb cake on a plate with powdered sugar." class="wp-image-140974" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20.jpg 1200w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20-480x600.jpg 480w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20-819x1024.jpg 819w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20-768x960.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20-150x188.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1500" src="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20.jpg" alt="A thick slice of new york style crumb cake on a plate with powdered sugar." class="wp-image-140974" srcset="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20.jpg 1200w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20-480x600.jpg 480w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20-819x1024.jpg 819w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20-768x960.jpg 768w, https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20-150x188.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://www.garlicandzest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/New-York-Crumb-Coffeecake-20.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<p>This coffee cake with thick cinnamon streusel crumble goes great with a steaming cup of coffee or tea and is perfect with orange juice or morning cocktails like <a href="https://www.garlicandzest.com/cranberry-mimosa/">Cranberry Mimosas</a>, <a href="https://www.garlicandzest.com/ruby-thyme-spritzer/">Grapefruit Mimosas (grapefruit juice cocktails)</a> or this <a href="https://www.garlicandzest.com/sparkling-elderflower-prosecco-cocktail-with-honey-syrup/">Elderflower Prosecco Cocktail</a>.</p>



